{"published time": "2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00", "images": ["https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/albacete.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/albacete.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/8.Marz2024_Leipzig-2.cleaned-1024x794.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/8.Marz2024_Leipzig-4.cleaned-768x1024.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Koln1-1024x768.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Altendorf1-1024x768.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Altendorf2-1024x768.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Hamburg-8March-Posters.jpg", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Denmark.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trondheim_1.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trondheim_2.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trondheim_3.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trondheim_7.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trondheim_8-1024x682.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trondheim_9-1024x682.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trondheim_11-1024x682.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trondheim_13.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Finland_Poster.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Finland_1.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Finland_2.webp"], "content": "<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n<img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"high\" height=\"768\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000000.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000000.png\" width=\"1024\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"entry-content\">\n<p>We share an overview of actions and statements that we have seen for the 8<sup>th</sup> March this year.</p>\n<p>Regarding Turkey we have already shared a <a href=\"https://redherald.org/2024/03/04/turkey-activities-and-statement-for-the-8th-of-march/\">statement</a> by the New Democratic Women (YDK) as well as activities carried out by them in Istanbul. We have also shared a <a href=\"https://redherald.org/2024/03/03/turkey-call-for-the-8th-of-march/\">statement</a> by the Purple-Red collective. YDK has also published a poster and put up dazibaos mobilizing for the 8<sup>th</sup> of March in Izmir.</p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-dnt=\"true\" data-width=\"550\"><p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"tr\">8 Mart D\u00fcnya Emek\u00e7i Kad\u0131nlar G\u00fcn\u00fc\u2019nde \u0130zmir Alsancak\u2019tay\u0131z!<br/><br/>\ud83d\udccdT\u00fcrkan Saylan K\u00fclt\u00fcr Merkezi<br/>\ud83d\udcc68 Mart<br/>\ud83d\udd5518.00 <a href=\"https://t.co/n8xrRmF7GH\">pic.twitter.com/n8xrRmF7GH</a></p>\u2014 Yeni Demokrat Kad\u0131n (@ydkresmi) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ydkresmi/status/1765356637924081783?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">March 6, 2024</a></blockquote><script async=\"\" charset=\"utf-8\" src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\"></script>\n</div></figure>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-dnt=\"true\" data-width=\"550\"><p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"tr\">Duvar gazetelerimizle \u0130zmir sokaklar\u0131nday\u0131z. <br/><br/>8 Mart D\u00fcnya Emek\u00e7i Kad\u0131nlar G\u00fcn\u00fc'nde \u0130zmir Alsancak'ta bulu\u015fuyoruz, sen de gel!<br/><br/>\ud83d\udccdAlsancak T\u00fcrkan Saylan K\u00fclt\u00fcr Merkezi<br/>\ud83d\udcc58 Mart Cuma<br/>\ud83d\udd5518.00 <a href=\"https://t.co/Sm1oTnniVw\">pic.twitter.com/Sm1oTnniVw</a></p>\u2014 Yeni Demokrat Kad\u0131n (@ydkresmi) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ydkresmi/status/1764954703807365169?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">March 5, 2024</a></blockquote><script async=\"\" charset=\"utf-8\" src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\"></script>\n</div></figure>\n<p>In Brazil, the People\u2019s Woman\u2019s Movement (MFP) have published a <a href=\"https://anovademocracia.com.br/movimento-feminino-popular-lanca-boletim-para-8-de-marco-de-2024/\">Bulletin</a> for the 8<sup>th</sup> of March. We have recently published an <a href=\"https://redherald.org/2024/03/04/brazil-the-inextinguishable-flame-of-the-battle-of-stalingrad/\">article</a> by the MFP on the victory of the Red Army in the battle of Stalingrad, with a particular focus on the heroic struggle of women.</p>\n<p>In Lyon, France, the People\u2019s Women\u2019s Committee has called for a meeting on the 7<sup>th</sup> of March.</p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-dnt=\"true\" data-width=\"550\"><p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"fr\">\ud83d\udccdLyon<br/>Rendez-vous ce jeudi 7 Mars 18h sur le campus PDA salle H109 pour le meeting du 8 Mars du Comit\u00e9 F\u00e9minin Populaire ! <a href=\"https://t.co/pNdMWtSjEj\">pic.twitter.com/pNdMWtSjEj</a></p>\u2014 Ligue de la Jeunesse R\u00e9volutionnaire (@LigueJ_R) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/LigueJ_R/status/1765331826443260390?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">March 6, 2024</a></blockquote><script async=\"\" charset=\"utf-8\" src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\"></script>\n</div></figure>\n<p>In the Spanish State, the newspaper Servir al Pueblo has published an editorial, which we have already translated to English, on how the State and imperialism sustain patriarchal violence.</p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-wp-embed is-provider-the-red-herald wp-block-embed-the-red-herald\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"KEipB6XDfq\"><a href=\"https://redherald.org/2024/03/03/spanish-state-servir-al-pueblo-the-state-and-imperialism-sustain-patriarchal-violence/\">Spanish State \u2013 Servir al Pueblo: The State and imperialism sustain patriarchal violence</a></blockquote><iframe class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"KEipB6XDfq\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"338\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" scrolling=\"no\" security=\"restricted\" src=\"https://redherald.org/2024/03/03/spanish-state-servir-al-pueblo-the-state-and-imperialism-sustain-patriarchal-violence/embed/#?secret=Y60Vp1e6tC#?secret=KEipB6XDfq\" style=\"position: absolute; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);\" title=\"\u201cSpanish State \u2013 Servir al Pueblo: The State and imperialism sustain patriarchal violence\u201d \u2014 The Red Herald\" width=\"600\"></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n<p>Servir al Pueblo has also published a translation into Spanish of a <a href=\"https://serviralpuebloperiodico.wordpress.com/2024/02/28/aurora-picornell-simbolo-de-mujer-comunista/\">document</a> by the MFP of Brazil, on the life and work of Aurora Picornell.</p>\n<p>Also a graffiti has been made in <a href=\"https://serviralpuebloperiodico.wordpress.com/2024/03/06/albacete-pintada-por-la-mujer-combatiente-palestina/\">Albacete</a>, with the slogan \u201cLong Live the Palestinian woman with a rifle in the hand!\u201d</p>\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9574\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"768\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000001.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000001.png\" width=\"1024\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Graffiti in Albacete, Spanish State. Source: Servir al Pueblo</figcaption></figure></div>\n<p>In Austria, Rote Fahne has <a href=\"https://www.rotefahne.at/post/heraus-zum-8-m%C3%A4rz-dem-internationalen-kampftag-der-frauen\">called for demonstrations</a> on the 8<sup>th</sup> of March in the cities of Wien, Linz and Innsbruck. We have previously published a translation of an article by Rote Fahne on the struggle for the oldest self-managed autonomous women\u2019s center in Europe</p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-wp-embed is-provider-the-red-herald wp-block-embed-the-red-herald\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"NC45A4Y2hC\"><a href=\"https://redherald.org/2024/03/02/austria-fz-stays-the-struggle-for-the-oldest-self-managed-autonomous-womens-center-in-europe-continues/\">Austria \u2013 FZ stays! \u2013 The struggle for the oldest self-managed autonomous women\u2019s center in Europe continues!</a></blockquote><iframe class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"NC45A4Y2hC\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"338\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" scrolling=\"no\" security=\"restricted\" src=\"https://redherald.org/2024/03/02/austria-fz-stays-the-struggle-for-the-oldest-self-managed-autonomous-womens-center-in-europe-continues/embed/#?secret=y2zKm5KzLb#?secret=NC45A4Y2hC\" style=\"position: absolute; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);\" title=\"\u201cAustria \u2013 FZ stays! \u2013 The struggle for the oldest self-managed autonomous women\u2019s center in Europe continues!\u201d \u2014 The Red Herald\" width=\"600\"></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n<p>From Germany we have published a translation of a call for the 8<sup>th</sup> of March by the Red Women\u2019s Committees<em>.</em></p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-wp-embed is-provider-the-red-herald wp-block-embed-the-red-herald\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"wU5xghaTKn\"><a href=\"https://redherald.org/2024/03/03/germany-call-for-8th-of-march/\">Germany: Call for 8th of March</a></blockquote><iframe class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"wU5xghaTKn\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"338\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" scrolling=\"no\" security=\"restricted\" src=\"https://redherald.org/2024/03/03/germany-call-for-8th-of-march/embed/#?secret=2KB9wdvX2V#?secret=wU5xghaTKn\" style=\"position: absolute; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);\" title=\"\u201cGermany: Call for 8th of March\u201d \u2014 The Red Herald\" width=\"600\"></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n<p><em>Several events have also been called for in different cities in Germany. Earlier this month there has been presentations in <a href=\"https://demvolkedienen.org/index.php/de/t-brd/8345-bremen-bremerhaven-veranstaltungen-und-demonstration-zum-internationalen-frauenkampftag\">Bremen</a>, <a href=\"https://demvolkedienen.org/index.php/de/t-proletarischer-feminismus/8348-nrw-mobilisierung-zum-8-maerz-2024\">Cologne and Buchum</a>. On the 7</em><em><sup>th</sup></em><em> of March there will be an event by the Red Women\u2019s Committee in Hamburg. On the 8</em><em><sup>th</sup></em><em> of March the Red Women\u2019s Committee has called for demonstrations in <a href=\"https://demvolkedienen.org/index.php/de/t-proletarischer-feminismus/8335-leipzig-mobilisierung-zum-8-maerz-2024\">Leipzig</a>, <a href=\"https://demvolkedienen.org/index.php/de/t-brd/8345-bremen-bremerhaven-veranstaltungen-und-demonstration-zum-internationalen-frauenkampftag\">Bremerhaven</a>, <a href=\"https://demvolkedienen.org/index.php/de/t-proletarischer-feminismus/8348-nrw-mobilisierung-zum-8-maerz-2024\">Essen and Cologne</a>. There has also been reports of mobilization for the events:</em></p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-1 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9556\" data-id=\"9556\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"794\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000002.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000002.png\" width=\"1024\"/></figure>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9557\" data-id=\"9557\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"1024\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000003.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000003.png\" width=\"768\"/></figure>\n<figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-caption wp-element-caption\"><em>Posters mobilizing for the 8<sup>th</sup> of March in Leipzig. Source: Dem Volke Dienen</em></figcaption></figure>\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9565\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"768\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000004.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000004.png\" width=\"1024\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><em>Posters mobilizing for the 8<sup>th</sup> of March in Cologne. Source: Dem Volke Dienen</em></figcaption></figure></div>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-2 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9558\" data-id=\"9558\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"768\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000005.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000005.png\" width=\"1024\"/></figure>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9559\" data-id=\"9559\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"768\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000006.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000006.png\" width=\"1024\"/></figure>\n<figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-caption wp-element-caption\"><em>Posters mobilizing for the 8<sup>th</sup> of March in Essen. Source: Dem Volke Dienen</em></figcaption></figure>\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9564\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"516\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 906px) 100vw, 906px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000007.jpg\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000007.jpg\" width=\"906\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><em>Posters mobilizing for the 8<sup>th</sup> of March in Hamburg. Source: Dem Volke Dienen</em></figcaption></figure></div>\n<p>In Italy, the news site Per la Democrazia Popolare has published a <a href=\"https://www.perlademocraziapopolare.com/per-un-otto-marzo-internazionalista-contro-il-fascismo-e-limperialismo/\">flyer</a> for an internationalist 8<sup>th</sup> of March against fascism and imperialism.</p>\n<p><em>We have previously <a href=\"https://redherald.org/2024/03/02/some-actions-for-the-8th-of-march-in-the-nordic-countries/\">reported</a> on actions for the 8th of March in Denmark, Norway and Finland. There are now reports of more actions in the Nordic countries.</em></p>\n<p><em>In Copenhagen, Denmark, <a href=\"https://socialistiskrevolution.wordpress.com/2024/03/06/kobenhavn-dazibaos-for-mobilisering-til-8-marts/\">dazibaos</a> with the slogans \u201cOut on the streets March 8!\u201d, \u201cAgainst imperialism and patriarchy!\u201d and \u201cFor a red class line in the women\u2019s movement!\u201d have been put up in proletarian neighborhoods.</em></p>\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9560\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"512\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000008.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000008.png\" width=\"768\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><em>Dazibao mobilizing for the 8<sup>th</sup> of March in Copenhagen, Denmark. Source: Socialistisk Revolution</em></figcaption></figure></div>\n<p><em>In Norway, Kampkomiteen has published a <a href=\"https://kampkomiteen.net/?p=6913\">call</a> for the 8</em><em><sup>th</sup></em><em> of March, with events and demonstrations in the cities off Oslo, Bergen, Trondheim and Kristiansand. There are also several reports of posters being put up in the Region of <a href=\"https://kampkomiteen.net/?p=6934\">Tr\u00f8ndelag</a>. The posters mobilizing for the 8</em><em><sup>th</sup></em><em> of March were put up in the regional capital, <a href=\"https://kampkomiteen.net/?p=6890\">Trondheim</a>, as well as several other places. You can read more reports <a href=\"https://kampkomiteen.net/?p=6902\">here</a> and <a href=\"https://kampkomiteen.net/?p=6938\">here</a>.</em></p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-3 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9566\" data-id=\"9566\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"576\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000009.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000009.png\" width=\"768\"/></figure>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9567\" data-id=\"9567\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"576\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000010.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000010.png\" width=\"768\"/></figure>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9568\" data-id=\"9568\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"594\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000011.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000011.png\" width=\"768\"/></figure>\n<figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-caption wp-element-caption\"><em>Posters mobilizing for the 8<sup>th</sup> of March in Saupstad, south of Trondheim, Norway. Source: Kampkomiteen</em></figcaption></figure>\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9569\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"1000\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000012.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000012.png\" width=\"750\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><em>Posters mobilizing for the 8<sup>th</sup> of March in Heimdal, south of Trondheim, Norway. Source: Kampkomiteen</em></figcaption></figure></div>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-4 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9570\" data-id=\"9570\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"682\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000013.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000013.png\" width=\"1024\"/></figure>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9571\" data-id=\"9571\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"682\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000014.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000014.png\" width=\"1024\"/></figure>\n<figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-caption wp-element-caption\"><em>Posters mobilizing for the 8<sup>th</sup> of March in Malvik, Norway. Source: Kampkomiteen</em></figcaption></figure>\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9572\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"682\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000015.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000015.png\" width=\"1024\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><em>Posters mobilizing for the 8<sup>th</sup> of March in Stj\u00f8rdal, Norway. Source: Kampkomiteen</em></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9573\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"550\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000016.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000016.png\" width=\"850\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><em>Posters mobilizing for the 8<sup>th</sup> of March in Trondheim, Norway. Source: Kampkomiteen</em></figcaption></figure></div>\n<p><em>In Finland, the news site Punalippu has shared calls for demonstrations in <a href=\"https://punalippu.noblogs.org/post/2024/02/29/hki-mielenosoitus-kansainvalisena-naistenpaivana/\">Helsinki</a> and <a href=\"https://punalippu.noblogs.org/post/2024/02/26/tre-mielenosoitus-kansainvalisena-naistenpaivana/\">Tampere</a>. The news site has also published a <a href=\"https://punalippu.noblogs.org/post/2024/03/04/tre-julisteita-kansainvalisen-naistenpaivan-alla/\">poster</a> mobilizing for the 8<sup>th</sup> of March, which has been put up in Tampere.</em></p>\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9563\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"659\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 419px) 100vw, 419px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000017.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000017.png\" width=\"419\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><em>\u201cInternational Women\u2019s Day 8.3. \u2013 Down with imperialism and patriarchy! \u2013 Long live the armed struggle of the national resistance of the Palestinian people! \u2013 Long live proletarian feminism! \u2013 Unite under Maoism!\u201d. Source: Punalippu</em></figcaption></figure></div>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-5 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9561\" data-id=\"9561\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"476\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000018.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000018.png\" width=\"768\"/></figure>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9562\" data-id=\"9562\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"524\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000019.png\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-06T23-55-00-00-00/000019.png\" width=\"768\"/></figure>\n<figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-caption wp-element-caption\"><em>Posters mobilizing for the 8<sup>th</sup> of March in Tampere, Finland. Source: Punalippu</em></figcaption></figure>\n</div>", "source": "https://redherald.org/2024/03/06/actions-and-statements-for-the-8th-of-march/", "type": "article", "title": "Actions and Statements for the 8th of March \u2013 The Red Herald", "description": "We share an overview of actions and statements that we have seen for the 8th March this year.", "modified time": "2024-03-06T21:54:38+00:00", "author": ["T.I."], "categories": ["Featured", "International"], "tags": ["8th of March"], "sections": ["Featured", "International", "8th of March", "English", "pll_65e8e67b87767"]}